Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @cashew nuts{25} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, pop into a #small bowl{}.

Meanwhile, bring a #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260} and pepper. Stir-fry until the chicken is golden brown and cooked through and the pepper has softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the garlic and ginger, then fry for ~{1%minute}.

While the chicken and noodles cook, pop the @hoisin sauce{64}, @honey{15}, @soy sauce{15} and @water for the sauce{50} into a small bowl.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Mix well and set aside.

Once everything's cooked, add the noodles, @mangetout{80}(trimmed) and hoisin glaze to the chicken.

Mix well to combine and cook until everything's piping hot and the sauce has thickened to coat the noodles, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt and @pepper if needed. Add a splash of @?water{} if you feel it needs it.

Share the hoisin chicken noodles between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the cashew nuts to finish.

Enjoy!